          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500; margin-top:2px !important">“Liberation Day” tariffs are out</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/president-trump-new-tariffs-100-countries.png" alt="President Trump has imposed new tariffs on over 100 countries" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;"><i>President Trump has imposed new tariffs on over 100 countries. Credits: The Economic Times</i></p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          Trump's "Liberation Day" tariffs intensify fears of a global trade war. Trump has announced a <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-03-04-2025-h1-1-slew-of-tariffs?source=website" target="_blank">slew of tariffs</a>, which include:</p>
          <ol style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5; margin-top:4px;margin-bottom:5px;">
          <li>A baseline 10% tariff on 100 countries will go into effect from April 5.</li>
          <li>Custom tariffs on 60 <i>worst offenders</i> will go into effect from April 9.</li>
          <li>25% tariff on all auto imports.</li>
          </ol>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          The countries worst affected by the tariffs include China (54%), Cambodia (49%), and Vietnam (46%). Notably, Canada and Mexico were not targeted this time as the US felt the existing executive orders would deal with their situation.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;filter:blur(5px);">
          Trump argues these tariffs will stop Americans from being ripped off, pay off national debts, and increase domestic manufacturing. The US stock market reacted sharply to the tariffs. Dow futures plummeted  2.7%, S&P500 futures sank 3.9%, and NASDAQ 100 plunged 4.7%. The Asian markets also saw a dip corresponding to the announcement.</p>
          
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
